[gd_resource type="Resource" script_class="HandbookPage" load_steps=2 format=3]

[ext_resource type="Script" path="res://resources/HandbookPage.gd" id="1_page"]

[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_page")
page_id = "incidents"
title = "THREAT RECOGNITION CATALOG"
content = "[b][color=#006CFF]COMMON ATTACK PATTERNS[/color][/b]

• [b]PHISHING[/b]: Look for 'typosquatted' domains (e.g., [i]micros0ft.com[/i]) or urgent requests from 'Executives' using external email addresses.
• [b]MALWARE[/b]: General malicious software. Detected via [color=cyan]Terminal Scan[/color]. Simple infections require isolation and clean-up.
• [b]RANSOMWARE[/b]: A critical sub-type of Malware. Characterized by file encryption. Requires [color=cyan]Root Cause Verification[/color] and the [color=cyan]Decryption Tool[/color] to resolve.
• [b]DATA EXFILTRATION[/b]: Watch the SIEM Volume Graphs for massive, sustained outbound traffic spikes to unknown external IPs.
• [b]INSIDER THREAT[/b]: Unauthorized access attempts to high-value assets (Finance/Vault) by standard user accounts.

[b][color=#006CFF]EMERGENCY RESPONSE CODES[/color][/b]
• [b]CODE BLUE[/b]: Normal operations. 
• [b]CODE RED[/b]: Active breach or data loss in progress. 
• [b]CODE BLACK[/b]: Total SOC lockout / Administrative compromise."
